WEBVTT

00:00.968 --> 00:02.670
Previously on The Unit.
Cowboy,

00:02.736 --> 00:05.606
- you could buy me a beer.
- [ Grey ] I'm gonna spend
my leave with her.

00:05.673 --> 00:08.342
Charles, who the hell
is this girl?
I'm gonna marry her.

00:08.409 --> 00:11.845
- Do you think this is sudden?
- You know how your mother
always said you'll just know?

00:11.912 --> 00:13.781
- Who are you?
- I beg your pardon?

00:13.847 --> 00:17.218
Everything that you
have told her and me
has been a lie.

00:17.285 --> 00:21.322
And this company
you say you work for--
that doesn't exist.

00:21.389 --> 00:23.157
The president-elect's motorcade
has just been attacked.

00:23.224 --> 00:24.792
Is the president secure?

00:24.858 --> 00:27.228
Secret Service has lost
communication with
their men on the ground.

00:27.295 --> 00:29.830
- I need the last position
of that motorcade.
- Sir,

00:29.897 --> 00:32.733
members of your security detail
have betrayed you.

00:32.800 --> 00:35.503
- We are here to get you out.
- Are you a loyal American?

00:35.569 --> 00:38.739
Sir, that is one thing
in my nature
that is not a fault.

00:39.907 --> 00:42.310
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

00:43.277 --> 00:45.513
[ Plates Clink ]

00:46.480 --> 00:49.517
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

00:56.124 --> 00:58.292
[ Foreign Language ]

01:15.109 --> 01:17.545
[ Knocks ]

01:32.926 --> 01:35.296
[ Engine Starts ]

02:09.129 --> 02:11.665
[ Muffled Gunshots ]

02:38.426 --> 02:40.628
Hey.

02:40.694 --> 02:44.365
[ Speaking French ]

02:45.666 --> 02:47.635
[ French ]

02:53.207 --> 02:55.276
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]

02:59.980 --> 03:01.882
[ Ringing Continues ]

03:14.362 --> 03:16.464
[ Ringing Continues ]

03:27.575 --> 03:29.443
Ali.

03:29.510 --> 03:32.680
Ali.
[ Foreign Language ]

03:36.250 --> 03:38.452
Ah.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.495
[ Knocking ]
Ali.

04:21.762 --> 04:25.733
[ Chuckles ]
Ha! Told ya.

04:25.799 --> 04:28.802
- [ French ]
- [ Chuckles ]

04:28.869 --> 04:33.307
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

04:33.374 --> 04:37.110
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

04:37.177 --> 04:39.212
* See another dawn *

04:39.279 --> 04:41.715
* Through a daughter's eyes *

04:41.782 --> 04:45.553
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

04:58.466 --> 05:00.734
[ Dog Barks ]

05:01.835 --> 05:04.638
That's a nice-looking dog.
Is he friendly?

05:04.705 --> 05:06.774
Most animals bite
if provoked.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.379
I believe that's
some line out of a novel.

05:22.122 --> 05:24.958
[ Man ]
There are scheduled meetings
on Wednesday, Saturday.

05:25.025 --> 05:27.060
[ Man #2 ]
The prime minister.
Yes.

05:27.127 --> 05:29.096
All day?

05:32.866 --> 05:34.868
Mr. President.

05:36.470 --> 05:39.873
Can we get you a cup
of coffee or something?
Thank you, sir. I'm fine.

05:41.542 --> 05:44.878
Well, sometimes
you've just got to, uh--

05:46.414 --> 05:48.348
Sometimes you gotta
reach out to a friend.

05:48.416 --> 05:51.018
Always, sir.
Under any circumstances.

05:51.084 --> 05:53.821
What I've got here,
Sergeant Major,
is the borderline between...

05:53.887 --> 05:56.790
necessities of state
and personal interest.

05:56.857 --> 05:59.793
I flunked philosophy, sir.
You just tell me
what you want me to do.

05:59.860 --> 06:02.530
Cartwright.

06:02.596 --> 06:05.232
"Elias Brandt:
The New Philanthropy."

06:05.298 --> 06:09.470
Yes. And part of that
philanthropy, as you may know,
was my campaign.

06:09.537 --> 06:11.939
Well, sir--
[ Chuckles ]
all in a good cause.

06:12.005 --> 06:14.207
Yeah, well, now it's
piper paying time.
Uh-huh.

06:14.274 --> 06:16.877
My friend, Mr. Brandt,

06:16.944 --> 06:18.912
is a survivor
of the Holocaust.

06:18.979 --> 06:22.082
His family died
at Bergen-Belsen.

06:23.383 --> 06:26.620
Klaus Kolben, medical doctor,
Berlin, 1938.

06:26.687 --> 06:29.289
Klaus Kolben of the S.S.

06:29.356 --> 06:31.659
Camp doctor
of the Belsen death camp.

06:31.725 --> 06:34.261
That would be the man
who killed my friend's family.

06:34.327 --> 06:37.598
We've just received
intelligence he may still
be alive-- in Switzerland.

06:38.866 --> 06:41.034
And my friend received
the same intelligence...

06:41.101 --> 06:43.403
and has dispatched
his people to find Kolben.

06:43.471 --> 06:46.339
To kidnap him.
My understanding is
they want to kill him.

06:46.406 --> 06:50.944
I cannot let my friend
send an armed force into
the territory of an ally.

06:51.011 --> 06:52.513
And politically,

06:52.580 --> 06:55.583
I can't afford to alienate
my biggest supporter.

06:55.649 --> 06:59.419
- Sounds to me
like it's time to punt.
- Well, that's exactly right.

06:59.487 --> 07:01.689
That's right, my friend.

07:01.755 --> 07:04.525
My team, sir,
is due for a little leave.

07:04.592 --> 07:06.994
Is that so?
It is so, sir.

07:07.060 --> 07:09.930
Although it can be
of no interest to you.

07:12.966 --> 07:16.036
It's great
to see you again, sir.

07:19.507 --> 07:23.777
Last known photo of Kolben
before his escape.

07:23.844 --> 07:27.515
Computer rendition of his
possible appearance today.

07:29.817 --> 07:33.086
Here are clean passports
for you and your team.

07:33.153 --> 07:35.989
Here are the funds
and your contact at
the World Court at The Hague.

07:37.725 --> 07:40.427
Get him there,
get him off the playing field.

07:40.494 --> 07:42.195
For the love of God,
don't get caught.

07:43.396 --> 07:45.465
The last Nazi.

07:47.400 --> 07:49.269
Mister,

07:49.336 --> 07:51.471
you're about to
have some company.

07:51.539 --> 07:53.641
[ Door Closes ]

08:00.614 --> 08:02.716
[ Cricket Chirping ]

08:14.728 --> 08:16.830
[ Man Whispers ]
Tom.

08:18.065 --> 08:20.868
[ Man ]
Fella said to the old man,

08:22.369 --> 08:24.237
"What would you wish for...

08:25.405 --> 08:28.108
if you were 18 again?"

08:28.175 --> 08:30.678
Old man said,

08:30.744 --> 08:32.846
"Not another thing.

08:33.881 --> 08:36.750
"Jumping out of airplanes,

08:36.817 --> 08:40.120
"every woman in the world,

08:40.187 --> 08:42.189
kicking the door down."

08:42.255 --> 08:44.424
Kicking the door down.

08:44.491 --> 08:48.862
My wife asked me
what I would give
if I could go back.

08:50.330 --> 08:53.767
Of course I lied to her.
Of course you did, sir.

08:53.834 --> 08:56.904
The act of a gentleman.

09:01.842 --> 09:04.578
You know who
pinned those on me?

09:04.645 --> 09:06.647
Yes, sir. I do.

09:06.714 --> 09:09.416
I'd like to
pin them on you, Tom.

09:09.482 --> 09:13.721
It's been authorized,
and it's a fact,
if you will accept.

09:15.522 --> 09:17.591
It would mean
leaving the Unit.

09:17.658 --> 09:19.760
Unit's a colonel's
billet, Tom.

09:21.128 --> 09:23.631
Would you like to
think about it?

09:23.697 --> 09:26.399
Yes, sir. I would.

09:26.466 --> 09:28.568
Thank you, sir.

09:35.876 --> 09:38.812
It's a hell of a thing.

09:40.648 --> 09:42.750
So was Phuong Thai, old friend.

09:43.651 --> 09:45.753
Yes, sir.

09:50.223 --> 09:52.325
You gotta be careful
what you wish for.

09:54.227 --> 09:56.129
[ Woman ]
What?

09:57.330 --> 09:59.800
Said you gotta be careful
what you wish for.

10:07.240 --> 10:09.209
Not in my army?

10:13.346 --> 10:16.216
I was raised on this.
I see no reason to switch now.

10:28.195 --> 10:31.665
[ Man ]
What the hell you looking at?
[ Woman ] What?

10:31.732 --> 10:33.200
I wasn't looking at--
Not you.

10:33.266 --> 10:35.302
Him.

10:35.368 --> 10:38.138
What the hell
you looking at, pal?
You eyeballing me?

10:38.205 --> 10:41.374
What are you, a fruit?
What are you,
a fruit like your father?

10:41.441 --> 10:44.144
- Do you know why
your mother left him?
- Shut up.

10:45.112 --> 10:46.714
No. Leave me alone!
Huh? Huh?

10:46.780 --> 10:49.182
Just leave me alone!
I'm trying to teach
the boy something!

10:49.249 --> 10:51.952
Leave me alone!
I don't know why
I stay with you!

10:52.019 --> 10:54.187
Oh, yes, you do.
Come here.

10:54.254 --> 10:56.156
Leave me alone.

10:59.226 --> 11:01.128
[ Glass Clinks ]

11:22.983 --> 11:25.652
Canadian Regional
Television Service.

11:25.719 --> 11:30.090
I'm sorry. We had an appointment
with Monsieur Sal so-and-so
to view the house.

11:30.157 --> 11:33.426
That's right.
Anybody, you muffle the name,

11:33.493 --> 11:36.764
99-to-1, they'll come back
at you and deliver it to you.

11:36.830 --> 11:39.299
"Oh. You mean Mr. Jones."
"Uh-huh."

11:41.168 --> 11:43.703
Ah. Here we go.

11:51.879 --> 11:54.447
[ Bell Tolling In Distance ]

12:02.790 --> 12:05.592
[ Sighs ]
"Fair thee well,
Old Joe Clark."

12:05.658 --> 12:07.427
"Good-bye, Betsy Brown."

12:07.494 --> 12:10.097
Shut up. I'm thinkin'.
[ Tolling Continues ]

12:12.132 --> 12:14.167
[ Mack ]
No good deed goes unpunished.

12:14.234 --> 12:17.370
No. If this guy is here,
we're gonna get him.

12:17.437 --> 12:19.773
- And if he's not?
- If he's not, then he's not.

12:19.840 --> 12:22.009
I--
I'm thinking.

12:22.075 --> 12:23.944
I feel naked
without the weapons.

12:24.011 --> 12:26.847
Well, my heart's full
of sympathy for you.
All right.

12:26.914 --> 12:30.417
Our man wasn't at the house
because the house
is no longer with us.

12:30.483 --> 12:32.685
Fire department report.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.588
You can just go in and get this?
It's Switzerland.
They keep everything.

12:35.655 --> 12:39.960
"House, in spite of efforts of
the local, burnt to the ground.
There were no casualties."

12:40.027 --> 12:43.230
All right. So, one:
Our man wasn't there.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.765
- Two: Where was he and why?
- [ Knocks ]

12:47.767 --> 12:49.937
Mmm.

12:51.171 --> 12:53.140
This is the doctor
for our quarry.

12:53.206 --> 12:55.175
He might be able
to lead us to Kolben.

12:55.242 --> 12:58.245
- And where's
the good doctor now?
- Um, hold on.

12:58.311 --> 13:00.413
I got Betty Blue on the line.
He's-- Hold one.

13:00.480 --> 13:02.349
Dr. Franz Wissen.

13:02.415 --> 13:05.485
Tuesdays he's at
the free clinic.
This address.

13:05.552 --> 13:07.988
All right. Let's--
News from outlying areas.

13:08.055 --> 13:10.690
Go.

13:10.757 --> 13:13.060
Looks like the opposition
has shown up.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.863
- Another news truck?
- Affirmative.

13:19.399 --> 13:23.236
- Are they real?
- No. Phony-baloney.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.839
Whatever we're planning to do,
we'd better do it now.

13:25.906 --> 13:28.808
'Cause I think they just
got the same idea.

13:31.678 --> 13:33.813
Let's go.

13:39.019 --> 13:41.288
No friend like
an old friend, eh?

13:42.990 --> 13:45.058
Ain't that the truth?

13:46.894 --> 13:48.896
Did you have something
to do with this?

13:50.730 --> 13:52.799
I'm not as powerful
as you think I am.

13:52.866 --> 13:56.569
Uh-huh.
Women are not as powerful
as you think they are.

13:56.636 --> 13:59.506
Is that true?
Yes, that's true.

13:59.572 --> 14:01.608
And I'll tell you one more.

14:04.044 --> 14:06.846
There's not one whit of
difference between any of us.

14:07.881 --> 14:10.583
It's just Betty and Veronica.

14:10.650 --> 14:12.452
All an illusion.

14:13.653 --> 14:15.555
If I take this star--

14:17.490 --> 14:19.426
If I take this star--

14:19.492 --> 14:22.930
If you take the star,
you have to leave home.

14:22.996 --> 14:24.965
You have to leave the Unit.

14:25.032 --> 14:27.467
Think I don't understand?

14:27.534 --> 14:29.937
You have to leave home.

14:30.971 --> 14:33.040
Everybody has to leave home.

14:36.576 --> 14:39.846
I'm assumin'
the reason you came in,
you want to join the army.

14:39.913 --> 14:42.582
Well, here's the good news.
You got your
birth certificate on you.

14:42.649 --> 14:45.919
When you leave this room,
you'll never have to
go home again.

14:45.986 --> 14:47.887
Did I guess right?

14:49.789 --> 14:52.325
Here's what's
gonna happen to ya.
You get to be a man,

14:52.392 --> 14:54.995
which means you're gonna
learn to use a weapon.

14:55.062 --> 14:58.765
In your travels,
you will have more women
than you know what to do with.

14:58.831 --> 15:01.134
And whatever son of a bitch
you've been dealing with,

15:01.201 --> 15:03.971
should you see him again,
I guaran-freaking-tee you,

15:04.037 --> 15:06.039
you will look upon him
with pity,

15:06.106 --> 15:09.642
and he will look
upon you with fear.

15:12.212 --> 15:14.347
And you get to serve
your country.

15:17.884 --> 15:19.919
So what the hell
are you waiting for?

15:26.960 --> 15:28.996
One day,

15:29.062 --> 15:31.298
if the enemy don't kill ya,

15:31.364 --> 15:34.301
or you're not blown to bits
by your own forces...

15:34.367 --> 15:37.937
or knifed by a whore
or something,

15:39.239 --> 15:41.374
you may live to be a general.

16:11.038 --> 16:13.840
[ Grey On Earpiece ]
Snake Doc, the opposition
has advanced to square two.

16:13.906 --> 16:16.443
They are two minutes
behind you.
Roger that.

16:16.509 --> 16:19.079
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

16:20.380 --> 16:23.116
[ Speaking German ]
[ Phone Ringing ]

16:23.183 --> 16:25.252
[ Woman Speaking German ]

16:27.054 --> 16:29.022
[ Phone Rings ]

16:29.089 --> 16:31.191
[ Woman Speaking German ]

16:36.229 --> 16:40.067
[ Phone Rings ]
[ Woman Speaking German ]

16:45.038 --> 16:47.340
[ Chattering ]

16:48.975 --> 16:51.744
- [ Intercom Beeps ]
- [ Woman On P.A.
Speaking German ]

17:00.153 --> 17:03.190
- [ Intercom Beeps ]
- [ Woman On P.A.
Speaking German ]

17:08.561 --> 17:12.065
[ Phone Rings ]
Excuse me.
Do you speak English?

17:12.132 --> 17:14.033
[ Grunts Softly ]
Yes.

17:14.101 --> 17:18.605
I'm sorry to intrude.
It's-- It's not my place,
as I am not your doctor.

17:18.671 --> 17:21.040
[ Grunts ]
Yes.

17:21.108 --> 17:23.243
May I?

17:24.744 --> 17:26.213
Oh!

17:26.279 --> 17:29.549
No, no, no.
It's okay. It's okay.
Please, what is it?

17:29.616 --> 17:33.420
Now, if your doctor
has discussed this
with you, forgive me.

17:33.486 --> 17:36.089
- But you know you have cancer.
- What?

17:36.156 --> 17:38.991
As I'm not your physician, I--
If you want me
to consult with him--

17:39.058 --> 17:40.593
I have cancer?

17:40.660 --> 17:42.929
[ German ]
Please.

17:42.995 --> 17:45.532
No, no, no, no, no.
It is treatable.

17:45.598 --> 17:48.501
And I think it's likely
that we've caught it in time,
but-- Excuse me.

17:48.568 --> 17:51.871
Put Frau Bergen in her room.
I need Frau Bergen's charts.

17:51.938 --> 17:53.440
Do you
speak English?
Yes.

17:56.075 --> 17:58.445
- Ja.
- [ German ]

17:58.511 --> 18:00.547
I will speak to you
in a moment.

18:07.954 --> 18:10.089
[ Doorbell Buzzes ]

18:13.460 --> 18:16.896
May I help you?
I'm looking for
Ms. Molly Bechet.

18:16.963 --> 18:19.766
Would that be you?
I'm Molly Bechet.

18:19.832 --> 18:23.069
I wonder if I could talk to you
about some aircraft.

18:23.136 --> 18:24.904
Well, I'm
the administrative head.

18:24.971 --> 18:28.875
I know.
You're the administrative
head of, uh,

18:28.941 --> 18:31.378
AeroDyne Alliance.

18:31.444 --> 18:33.946
Been in the aircraft
business long?

18:34.013 --> 18:36.183
Uh, mister--
Uh, my name's Carson.

18:36.249 --> 18:39.186
I've been in the aircraft
business some myself.

18:39.252 --> 18:42.222
Mr. Carson,
how may I help you today?

18:42.289 --> 18:45.825
Well, Ms. Bechet,

18:45.892 --> 18:48.528
I'd like to buy you out.

18:48.595 --> 18:50.330
[ Chuckles ]
You're joking.

18:50.397 --> 18:54.634
When was the last time
you heard somebody from Texas
joke about money?

18:54.701 --> 18:59.606
Well, I-I don't think
the business is for sale.
Oh. Well, that's unusual.

18:59.672 --> 19:01.974
What other reason is there
for a business,

19:02.041 --> 19:04.244
uh, except to make money?

19:04.311 --> 19:06.946
Or maybe I missed something
when I was growing up.

19:07.013 --> 19:08.915
Mr. Carson.

19:10.250 --> 19:12.319
Did you ever notice
the similarity between...

19:12.385 --> 19:16.155
a negotiation
and a... seduction?

19:16.223 --> 19:18.258
I hope I'm not
offending you by that.

19:18.325 --> 19:20.393
Uh--
One person
wants one thing.

19:20.460 --> 19:22.495
The other person
wants something else.

19:22.562 --> 19:26.333
And both parties
have to keep
their desires hidden.

19:26.399 --> 19:29.669
Why do they do that?
Oh, to make a better deal.

19:30.670 --> 19:33.072
Maybe that's why
I never married.

19:33.139 --> 19:36.075
- You married, Ms. Bechet?
- Yes, I am.

19:36.142 --> 19:38.845
Your husband have
something to do with
this business, does he?

19:38.911 --> 19:42.482
Yes. He's my partner.
Well, maybe you oughta call him
and ask him to come down here.

19:42.549 --> 19:44.917
He's out of town.
Oh.

19:44.984 --> 19:48.655
Well, then, uh, maybe
you could surprise him.

19:48.721 --> 19:53.426
Tell him all his dreams
have come true.

19:53.493 --> 19:57.964
Sadly, Mr. Carson,
he dreams of his career
in aviation.

19:58.030 --> 19:59.799
My name mean
anything to you?

19:59.866 --> 20:01.968
I'm sorry, no.
No.

20:02.034 --> 20:06.373
- Man that works for you--
he never mentioned my name?
- A man that works for me?

20:06.439 --> 20:08.708
- He didn't mention my name?
- I'm afraid not.

20:08.775 --> 20:11.944
Mm-hmm.

20:12.011 --> 20:15.615
You know the most
interesting thing that
ever happened to me?

20:15.682 --> 20:18.551
Mr. Carson, why are you here?

20:18.618 --> 20:22.822
Uh, a bunch of fellas-- and
this was in another country--
they put me up against a wall.

20:22.889 --> 20:27.059
I believe the technical term
for that is a firing squad.

20:27.126 --> 20:30.397
Now, the man in charge
I knew...

20:30.463 --> 20:32.765
was not gonna give
the command to fire.

20:32.832 --> 20:36.269
He was caught.
He didn't want to kill me.

20:36.336 --> 20:38.771
But he had orders.

20:38.838 --> 20:42.775
And his head...
was on the block.

20:42.842 --> 20:46.078
The reason I'm bringing
this up is, uh,

20:46.145 --> 20:50.149
because you have the same kind
of expression on your face
that he did.

20:50.216 --> 20:52.585
And what is that?

20:55.187 --> 20:59.659
My principal
has somehow got involved
in this business.

20:59.726 --> 21:01.628
And, Ms. Bechet,

21:01.694 --> 21:05.298
this business
does not exist.

21:05.365 --> 21:08.768
Mr. Carson, that's not true.
I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to ask you to leave.

21:08.835 --> 21:11.137
Ms. Bechet,
I am not your enemy.

21:11.203 --> 21:16.809
I am a man who spent
his entire adult life
in and around aircraft.

21:16.876 --> 21:19.278
Now, this place here--

21:19.346 --> 21:21.448
it's make-believe.

21:21.514 --> 21:25.184
I don't know why.
I've got my suspicions,
but, uh,

21:25.251 --> 21:30.323
there's only two reasons
in the world to get
in the aircraft business.

21:30.390 --> 21:32.559
Number one is money.

21:32.625 --> 21:35.395
Now, that's understandable,
but, uh, it's foolish,

21:35.462 --> 21:39.098
because it's a good way
to go completely broke.

21:39.165 --> 21:43.636
Number two
is a love of airplanes.

21:43.703 --> 21:45.772
You ain't got
any airplanes.

21:47.006 --> 21:50.009
So, that leaves money.

21:50.076 --> 21:53.380
Now, you look like
an intelligent woman to me.
Mr. Carson,

21:53.446 --> 21:55.815
I am an intelligent woman.

21:55.882 --> 21:58.985
And I'll be damned
if I can figure
what you're getting at.

21:59.051 --> 22:01.754
Well, here it is.

22:01.821 --> 22:06.893
This is my check,
and that is my signature.

22:06.959 --> 22:08.795
You fill in the amount.

22:10.363 --> 22:14.601
I'm paying you to go away.

22:14.667 --> 22:17.804
[ Charlotte ]
Yep. You gotta be careful
what you wish for.

22:17.870 --> 22:20.006
What?

22:20.072 --> 22:23.042
I said we have to be careful
what we wish for.

22:24.511 --> 22:26.413
We have to be careful
about everything.

22:26.479 --> 22:29.348
[ Exhales ]
Yes, that's true.

22:31.150 --> 22:33.085
And then what remains?

22:33.152 --> 22:34.987
What remains?

22:36.489 --> 22:38.658
Not self-pity.
Oh, no.

22:38.725 --> 22:42.061
You'd never pity yourself
because you have a choice.

22:42.128 --> 22:44.864
No.

22:44.931 --> 22:47.667
I take the star,
I have to leave the Unit.

22:47.734 --> 22:50.169
Betty and Veronica, Tom.

22:50.236 --> 22:52.304
It's the same thing.

22:52.371 --> 22:54.240
And a life without illusions?

22:54.306 --> 22:56.275
The fact is--

22:56.342 --> 23:00.580
[ Inhales, Exhales Deeply ]
Fact is--

23:02.214 --> 23:04.116
My poor Tom.

23:06.285 --> 23:08.721
Do you know why people
kill themselves?

23:11.223 --> 23:15.595
Yes, I do.
They kill themselves because
they can't stand living.

23:17.830 --> 23:20.733
Everything I ever
wished for was a ruse.

23:22.435 --> 23:24.704
Everything I ever
worked for was a lie.

23:24.771 --> 23:26.506
It is what you say it is.

23:27.907 --> 23:30.477
No. No.

23:31.444 --> 23:33.613
No.

23:49.829 --> 23:51.631
[ Ticking ]

24:25.331 --> 24:28.200
** [ Rock ]

24:28.267 --> 24:31.938
[ Chattering ]
** [ Man Singing, Indistinct ]

24:44.383 --> 24:46.318
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

24:46.385 --> 24:48.921
Oh!
** [ Continues ]

24:50.923 --> 24:54.561
* And you do as you please *

24:54.627 --> 24:58.430
* You say what you like **

24:58.497 --> 25:00.667
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]

25:12.779 --> 25:15.014
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

25:29.696 --> 25:31.698
All right, gents.
Coming your way.

25:33.299 --> 25:35.201
Redcap, how you doin'?

25:35.267 --> 25:37.637
[ Phone Rings ]

25:37.704 --> 25:39.271
Man inside.
What have you got?

25:40.573 --> 25:42.441
Hellhounds coming up.
You guys coming out?

25:42.508 --> 25:44.443
[ German ]

25:44.510 --> 25:46.813
No. We're gonna
be here a while.

25:49.682 --> 25:52.118
The last of
Mrs. Bergen's forms.

25:52.184 --> 25:54.854
Thank you.
Is there anything else,
Doctor?

25:54.921 --> 25:57.356
Yes. I had an appointment
to see Dr. Wissen.
Of course.

25:57.423 --> 25:58.925
One moment, please.

26:04.997 --> 26:08.067
- Here they come. Go.
- [ Engine Starts ]

26:13.339 --> 26:15.642
Give 'em hell.

26:18.377 --> 26:20.847
What the hell are you doing?
What are you doing?

26:20.913 --> 26:22.915
Oh--
Pulled out
right in front of us!

26:22.982 --> 26:25.017
Hey, hey. Everybody okay?
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to.

26:25.084 --> 26:28.688
- Just bought you some time.
- Need as much as you got.

26:28.755 --> 26:32.558
Yes. You need to see Dr. Wissen.
I'll be with you, Doctor,
in one moment.

26:32.625 --> 26:35.161
Well, you know,
we were supposed to meet
at the community room.

26:35.227 --> 26:37.797
If you could just--
Of course.
Right down the hall.

26:40.466 --> 26:42.334
Who are you?

26:52.144 --> 26:54.947
[ German ]

26:59.952 --> 27:02.221
Danke.
[ German ]

27:02.288 --> 27:04.623
[ Door Closes ]

27:04.691 --> 27:08.494
All right.
A lie is no good
if you hesitate.

27:08.560 --> 27:10.997
I have heard 60 years
of confessions.

27:11.063 --> 27:14.066
Who are you,
and what do you want?

27:14.133 --> 27:17.369
You're a soldier obviously.
Why is that obvious?

27:17.436 --> 27:19.972
I was a soldier.

27:23.743 --> 27:25.678
Do you know who this man is?

27:25.745 --> 27:29.982
Of course. It's Klaus Kolben.
You know what he did
during the war?

27:30.049 --> 27:32.985
I believe so.
It was fairly well known
after the war.

27:33.052 --> 27:35.454
You know he's still alive.

27:35.521 --> 27:37.356
How do you know
he is still alive?

27:37.423 --> 27:39.892
He's been seen here,
in this village,
at the house.

27:42.028 --> 27:44.096
What do you want with him?

27:44.163 --> 27:47.767
I want to save him.
There's a team here,
come to kill him.

27:47.834 --> 27:49.836
He was a monster.

27:49.902 --> 27:52.504
Yes, that's true.
Why do you want to save him?

27:52.571 --> 27:54.741
Hmm?

27:54.807 --> 27:57.076
Perhaps it is you
who have come here
to kill him.

27:57.143 --> 27:59.746
Father, I swear to you
I am not that man.

27:59.812 --> 28:01.480
Will you swear that to God?

28:01.547 --> 28:04.583
I do.

28:04.650 --> 28:08.354
Here's a computer rendition
of his probable
appearance today.

28:08.420 --> 28:11.490
It is probable,
but that is not, in fact,
how he looks.

28:11.557 --> 28:14.827
How do you know?
I've known him since
he first arrived here,

28:14.894 --> 28:18.297
40 years back.
[ Chuckles ]
You know where he is?

28:18.364 --> 28:21.033
Yes. He's down the hall.

28:25.604 --> 28:27.706
[ Phone Rings ]

28:34.380 --> 28:37.649
[ Man ]
What? Take it easy? You just
pulled out in front of us!

28:37.716 --> 28:39.418
[ Mack ]
Sorry.
You hit us!

28:39.485 --> 28:42.922
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
No, he's an idiot.

28:42.989 --> 28:45.091
You guys pulled out.
Hey.

28:45.157 --> 28:47.226
Whoa. Easy.
You've been drinkin'!

28:47.293 --> 28:49.328
You've been drinkin'!
Whoa, whoa.

28:49.395 --> 28:51.530
Whoa. Ho, ho.
They've been drinking.
Hey, hey, hey!

28:51.597 --> 28:54.867
They've been drinking. They
pulled out right in front of us.
Okay, okay.

28:54.934 --> 28:57.203
- Look. Look. They pulled out.
- Easy, sir. Easy.

28:57.269 --> 28:59.471
Write it down.

29:02.842 --> 29:05.077
Okay. Okay.
Let's go.

29:12.819 --> 29:15.955
Redcap, the defensive team's
going to the slammer.
How you holding?

29:16.022 --> 29:19.959
I need a sitrep.
Get to the boss, 'cause
we need a whole new exfil plan.

29:20.026 --> 29:23.129
- Can you talk?
- Uh, no.

29:23.195 --> 29:25.031
I'm sorry?

29:25.097 --> 29:28.600
- Oh, I-- I was talking to
myself. [ Clears Throat ]
- I beg your pardon?

29:28.667 --> 29:33.339
No, I was-- I was merely saying
that I don't know how long
we're going to be here.

29:33.405 --> 29:37.209
Okay. I got it.
You can't talk. Are you
any closer to the package?

29:37.276 --> 29:39.778
No.

29:39.846 --> 29:42.114
Have your communications
malfunctioned?

29:43.916 --> 29:45.918
I saw your men outside.

29:45.985 --> 29:48.320
You might tell them
that the Swiss,

29:48.387 --> 29:50.222
if they sit in cars,

29:50.289 --> 29:53.725
must speak to
one another earnestly...

29:53.792 --> 29:55.862
and not sit silent.

29:58.464 --> 30:01.000
Are you armed?

30:16.315 --> 30:19.051
The man you seek
has not long to live.

30:19.118 --> 30:21.420
He has confessed to me,
and it is not impossible...

30:21.487 --> 30:23.755
he will welcome the opportunity
to confess to you.

30:23.822 --> 30:27.826
Well, you know, I don't
want to hear his confession.
I just want--

30:28.660 --> 30:31.297
[ Grunting ]

30:42.208 --> 30:44.310
This check is for real?

30:46.512 --> 30:48.447
I think you know it is.

30:48.514 --> 30:51.117
You said that
the aviation business
was the best way to go broke.

30:51.183 --> 30:54.153
Ms. Bechet, do you know
how to design an airplane?

30:54.220 --> 30:56.688
No, no, no.
I-- I-- I know you don't.

30:56.755 --> 30:58.757
So I'm gonna tell ya.

30:58.824 --> 31:03.229
First of all,
you leave out anything
that ain't the plane,

31:03.295 --> 31:06.598
because the damn thing
has got to fly.

31:07.799 --> 31:10.502
Here it is.

31:10.569 --> 31:15.874
Your Mr. Charles Garza
wants to marry a woman
I care quite a bit about.

31:15.942 --> 31:18.077
[ Car Door Closes ]

31:25.017 --> 31:27.119
Hello, Joss.

31:29.388 --> 31:31.290
William?

31:31.357 --> 31:35.962
I was hoping we'd be
spared this eventuality.

31:36.028 --> 31:38.064
Well, many hopes
come to naught.

31:38.130 --> 31:40.066
I guess you're here
to see the boy.

31:41.667 --> 31:44.236
Honey, who are these people?

31:44.303 --> 31:46.372
They're in
the aviation business.

31:47.974 --> 31:51.944
You ask her to tell you
the cruising speed
of this airplane.

31:52.011 --> 31:54.646
Go ahead. Ask her.

31:59.485 --> 32:01.687
They're in
the aviation business.

32:01.753 --> 32:05.391
- No, honey. They ain't.
- This ain't like
the other time.

32:07.426 --> 32:09.395
Ma'am.

32:09.461 --> 32:11.097
Ma'am.

32:12.031 --> 32:14.066
[ Beeping ]

32:14.133 --> 32:17.169
Ma'am, let me start again.
What is--

32:20.206 --> 32:22.441
I've got to
keep my girl safe.

32:25.711 --> 32:27.713
So tell me what you want.

32:33.919 --> 32:36.088
[ Sighs ]

32:36.155 --> 32:39.158
I never asked you
for your sad story.

32:39.225 --> 32:41.960
Do you know why?
Why?

32:43.195 --> 32:45.431
Because it's tattooed
on your face.

32:46.765 --> 32:48.734
You thought,

32:48.800 --> 32:51.070
if you thought about it,

32:51.137 --> 32:54.373
that I loved you
for your beautiful act.

32:54.440 --> 32:56.642
My act, Charlotte?
Yes, that's right.

32:56.708 --> 32:59.245
Because of what you've done.

32:59.311 --> 33:02.181
But I don't love you
because of what you've done.

33:02.248 --> 33:04.250
Why do you love me?

33:04.316 --> 33:07.553
Well, yes.
That's the question.
If you're a fraud,

33:07.619 --> 33:10.622
if you're a traitor,

33:10.689 --> 33:14.160
if you must always,
always, always choose wrong,

33:14.226 --> 33:18.330
who could love a man
like that?
Who?

33:18.397 --> 33:19.965
Yes. Who?

33:20.032 --> 33:23.001
You know why I love you,
Charlotte?

33:24.036 --> 33:26.538
You don't love me, Tom.

33:26.605 --> 33:30.609
You loved me
when you thought I was Shiva,
destroyer of all worlds.

33:31.943 --> 33:33.879
That's who you could love.

33:33.945 --> 33:36.348
Or some Russian hooker.

33:36.415 --> 33:38.850
That's who
you could love, Tom--

33:38.917 --> 33:40.986
who ratified your faith
in women.

33:41.053 --> 33:43.622
That's who you could love.

33:43.689 --> 33:45.591
The bad girl.

33:45.657 --> 33:48.294
Maybe that's the only kind
of woman there is.

33:48.360 --> 33:51.863
[ Crowd Chattering ]
Wouldn't that be comforting?

33:51.930 --> 33:55.234
** [ Rock ]

34:01.373 --> 34:03.642
[ Mother Giggling ]
[ Man ]
Come here, baby.

34:05.511 --> 34:07.946
[ Kissing ]

34:08.013 --> 34:10.249
[ Man ]
Oh, yeah, baby.
Yeah, baby.

34:13.619 --> 34:16.888
[ Sighs ]
[ Mother ]
You like that?

34:16.955 --> 34:18.924
That?
Uh-huh.

34:18.990 --> 34:21.059
[ Mother ]
What about this?

34:26.332 --> 34:28.267
Your man is inside?

34:30.236 --> 34:32.538
I don't know what
you're talking about.

34:32.604 --> 34:35.174
Are you part of
the killer team?

34:36.275 --> 34:38.644
Answer me, as,

34:38.710 --> 34:41.547
if you aren't,
your man is in trouble.

34:44.816 --> 34:48.720
- Call him.
- Are you part of
the opposition?

34:48.787 --> 34:50.789
No.

34:50.856 --> 34:53.992
I'm your ally.

34:54.059 --> 34:56.162
Scout's honor.

34:58.530 --> 35:01.433
Snake Doc. Snake Doc.
Come in, Snake Doc.

35:01.500 --> 35:04.436
What's out of the ordinary?

35:18.184 --> 35:21.086
That's Klaus Kolben.

35:21.153 --> 35:23.455
And I believe
they have your friend.

35:33.031 --> 35:36.001
[ Bridget On Earpiece ]
Betty Blue, do you have
eyes on a black Mercedes?

35:36.067 --> 35:38.136
They may have Snake Doc.

35:38.204 --> 35:40.239
[ Grey On Earpiece ]
Affirmative.

35:41.840 --> 35:43.742
[ Engine Starts ]

36:23.815 --> 36:25.717
[ Gate Clicks ]

36:44.536 --> 36:46.838
- They've got Jonas?
- Who's your friend?

36:46.905 --> 36:49.908
Someone who knows
the color of the door
to your shooting house.

36:49.975 --> 36:51.610
What is the color of the door?

36:51.677 --> 36:53.812
There is no door
in the shooting house.

36:55.046 --> 36:57.616
Why is that?

36:57.683 --> 37:00.018
It was awarded as a prize
in a shooting competition.

37:00.085 --> 37:01.487
Between?

37:03.221 --> 37:05.291
Your country and mine.

37:05.357 --> 37:07.659
Are you armed?

37:07.726 --> 37:10.362
Because I fear they mean
to kill your operator.

37:10.429 --> 37:12.998
Dirt Diver, Cool Breeze,
come on.
No.

37:13.064 --> 37:14.900
They're out of commission.

37:14.966 --> 37:17.102
Do you have a plan?
Yeah.

37:17.168 --> 37:21.473
I have a plan. You want to be
some help, or am I just
gonna use you for parts?

37:21.540 --> 37:23.609
We're gonna take him down.

37:23.675 --> 37:26.244
Dirt Diver, welcome back.

37:26.312 --> 37:29.581
- Transpo's waiting.
What's the plan?
- One thing at a time.

37:30.649 --> 37:32.551
[ Man ]
You're going to assault them...

37:32.618 --> 37:34.653
on Swiss national soil?

37:34.720 --> 37:36.888
What are they gonna do?
Send me to Vietnam?

37:39.124 --> 37:41.527
All right.

37:41.593 --> 37:43.629
In return for what?

37:53.705 --> 37:55.707
Done.

38:01.380 --> 38:03.782
Go. Have the team
stand by at the airport.

38:06.785 --> 38:08.754
You--

38:08.820 --> 38:10.756
You ram that gate.

38:22.033 --> 38:23.902
[ Engine Revving ]

38:31.042 --> 38:32.978
Top!
Good!

38:33.044 --> 38:35.080
Cut him loose.

38:44.089 --> 38:46.425
Thanks.

38:56.167 --> 38:58.103
I've been waiting for you.

38:58.169 --> 39:00.439
Yeah?

39:00.506 --> 39:02.541
How long you been
waiting for me?

39:06.311 --> 39:08.414
Sixty years.

39:12.784 --> 39:14.753
How we getting out of here?

39:14.820 --> 39:17.355
I believe we can
get out the back.

39:17.423 --> 39:19.458
Betty Blue, take us out.

39:25.163 --> 39:27.866
Joss Morgan.

39:27.933 --> 39:30.135
Debutante.

39:30.201 --> 39:33.171
Owner of Morgan Aerospace.

39:33.238 --> 39:36.107
Billionaire with
a "B" for "Bravo."

39:36.174 --> 39:38.309
Debutante dropout,

39:38.376 --> 39:39.878
daredevil--

39:39.945 --> 39:41.913
This is the girl?
And apparently...

39:41.980 --> 39:44.583
the woman that our poor
Charlie is in love with.

39:44.650 --> 39:47.385
Ain't love grand?

39:47.453 --> 39:49.621
William Carson.

39:49.688 --> 39:53.425
William Carson
was her father's
crew chief in two wars.

39:53.492 --> 39:55.794
I understand.
He's trying to protect...

39:55.861 --> 39:57.796
what is, in effect,
his daughter...

39:57.863 --> 40:00.732
from the ravages of this world.

40:00.799 --> 40:02.934
Our Charlie.

40:03.001 --> 40:04.870
They love each other.

40:04.936 --> 40:08.474
- All the signs are present.
- William Carson
know who we are?

40:08.540 --> 40:11.710
I think he thinks
we're fortune hunters.

40:11.777 --> 40:13.879
Hmm.
He wants to buy the business.

40:18.249 --> 40:20.185
Why don't we
sell it to him?

40:20.251 --> 40:22.688
[ Laughs ]

40:28.393 --> 40:30.529
[ Sighs ]

40:35.534 --> 40:37.636
[ Sighing ]

40:39.971 --> 40:42.908
I'm sorry for everything
I've ever done.

40:45.911 --> 40:48.046
I know you are.

40:48.113 --> 40:49.981
Does that make me a fool?

40:50.048 --> 40:53.719
- No, you're not a fool.
- Then what am I?

40:53.785 --> 40:56.522
You're a man who's tired of
loathing himself.

40:58.824 --> 41:01.993
Will you help me,
Charlotte?
Yes, I will.

41:03.328 --> 41:06.097
Come here.

41:06.164 --> 41:08.066
Come here.

41:09.601 --> 41:11.169
It's all right.

41:13.271 --> 41:15.006
My love.

41:16.141 --> 41:18.376
My love.

41:18.443 --> 41:20.478
Thank you.

41:20.546 --> 41:23.915
[ Sighs Deeply ]

41:23.982 --> 41:25.717
Thank you.

41:31.089 --> 41:33.525
Three minutes,
my men will be here.

41:33.592 --> 41:35.794
Now? And now...

41:35.861 --> 41:39.565
"I execute you
in the name of
the Jewish people"? Huh?

41:39.631 --> 41:42.100
No, old man.
You're gonna stand trial.

41:42.167 --> 41:45.203
But--
What? Am I gonna have to
toss you for him?

41:45.270 --> 41:47.706
- Where were you planning
to take him?
- The Hague.

41:47.773 --> 41:49.875
Is he to die on the way?

41:49.941 --> 41:52.711
Not under my care.
Top, we're good to go.

41:52.778 --> 41:55.781
- [ Jonas ]
Let's go.
- All right.

41:55.847 --> 41:57.849
Redcap, Redcap, Redcap,
break free.

41:57.916 --> 41:59.417
Rendezvous at the airport.

41:59.484 --> 42:01.252
[ Jonas ]
Let's go.

42:01.319 --> 42:04.623
All right.
Time to pay up, old man.
I'm not ashamed of what I did.

42:04.690 --> 42:06.825
I could care less.

42:06.892 --> 42:09.995
Let's get us the hell
out of this fine country.

42:10.061 --> 42:12.764
[ Screaming ]

42:12.831 --> 42:16.001
[ Crowd Shouting, Chattering ]

42:49.400 --> 42:51.937
[ Siren Wailing ]
